        "description": {
            "value": "<p>Made of cobalt-colored steel rings that flow down the entire length of the garment, this <em>+1 resilient chain mail</em> includes an armored face covering. The armor is said to be based on the same armor once worn by Azure Leopard, one of Old-Mage Jatembe's magic warriors.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Activate</strong> <span class=\"action-glyph\">2</span> command, envision</p>\n<p><strong>Frequency</strong> once per day</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Effect</strong> You call upon the ferocity and grace of the leopard. The armor's rings flatten out to become a solid piece of flexible armor. You gain a +2 item bonus to Stealth checks and Intimidation checks to @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.Item.Demoralize], but take a -2 penalty to Diplomacy and Society checks.</p>\n<p>This lasts for 1 hour, but you can Activate the armor again to revert it back to its original form.</p>\n<p>@UUID[Compendium.pf2e.equipment-effects.Item.Effect: Leopard's Armor]</p>"
